# manual example: toggle inverts the state each trigger, which implements a
# clock divider by two when I1 is itself a clock. Manual: "A trigger here
# inverts the state of the flip flop. It changes 0 to 1 and 1 to 0."
# I1 rises at ticks 1, 3, 5 (period-2 clock); O1 should flip at each of those
# rising edges only, giving O1 a period of 4 -- half I1's frequency.
patch <<<
[flipflop]
    toggle = I1
    output = O1
>>>
@0 expect O1 0
@1 set I1 1
@1 expect O1 1
@2 set I1 0
@2 expect O1 1
@3 set I1 1
@3 expect O1 0
@4 set I1 0
@4 expect O1 0
@5 set I1 1
@5 expect O1 1
